<div class="toload definition">
<p><span class="envidentifier">Definition 1.2.33
<span style="font-weight:normal;">([<span class='ref' data-tag='MR3077869'></span>])</span></span>
A <em>distributive semigroup</em> is an inverse semigroup $S$ such that any two compatible elements $s,t\in S$ admit a join $s\lor t$, and for every $z\in S$, $z(s\lor t)=(zs)\lor (zt)$.
</p>
</div>